entry.title: Support visibility change notifications in AutofillProvider.java.
entry.content:
Android API level 27 (released December 2017) added support for

communicating visibility changes in forms during an ongoing Android

Autofill session.



This CL is the first in a series to add support for visibility changes

in WebView. It adds the required wiring between AutofillProvider.java

and the Android framework classes. It also adds setters and getters

for the visibility attribute of FormFields.



Low-Coverage-Reason: Pure wrapper class & more tests to be added later.

entry.title: [VC] Disable StopAllScreenShare.
entry.content:
There is currently a known crash caused by this.



(1) When a user is using google doc/slice, they can directly present from that page to a google Meet meeting.

(2) This will add two stopCallbacks for the same device to the display_media_stop_callbacks_.

(3) If the user stop the screen sharing from the webui, these two stop_callbacks will be removed correctly.

(4) However if the user uses the StopAllScreenShare button in the vc tray, these two stopCallbacks will both be called, and calling the second one will cause a crash.



This will influence any caller of StopMediaCapturing which contains

both ChromeOS (Video Conferencing) and Android (Digital Wellbeing).



This cl is only a temporary fix that not recording any stopcallbacks,

so no callback will be called when clicking on, therefore no crash.



We want to keep the change for easier cherry pick. We'll land a proper

fix later.



BUG=chromium:1479984



TEST='Tested on Dut manually"

entry.title: base: Make CreateDirectoryAndGetError set errno correctly on POSIX
entry.content:
CreateDirectoryAndGetError() returns successfully when the given path

already exists as a directory. To achieve this, it calls stat() when

mkdir() fails, which causes the errno to be overwritten by stat() when

the function returns false.

To get more informative logs with PLOG after the failure of

CreateDirectoryAndGetError() or CreateDirectory() (which internally

calls CreateDirectoryAndGetError()), this CL fixes

CreateDirectoryAndGetError() to set errno to be the one from mkdir()

right before returning false.

A similar fix has already been implemented for Windows in CL:1175782.

entry.title: Add WebP bpp (bits per pixel) histograms
entry.content:
Add a family of 23 Blink.DecodedImage.WebPDensity.Count.* histograms to

record the bits-per-pixel values of WebP images for various image sizes

(where size is the area = width * height).



- 9 histograms for image sizes 0.1 MP ~ 0.9 MP, in increments of 0.1 MP

- 13 histograms for image sizes 1 MP - 13 MP, in increments of 1 MP

- 1 histogram for image sizes > 13 MP



To avoid recording outliers in these histograms, only lossy, still (not

animated) images without an alpha plane are recorded in these

histograms.



The histograms are updated when the images are successfully decoded.



Change the comparison

demux_state_ <= WEBP_DEMUX_PARSING_HEADER

to the equivalent comparison

demux_state_ < WEBP_DEMUX_PARSED_HEADER

and change

DCHECK_GT(demux_state_, WEBP_DEMUX_PARSING_HEADER)

to

DCHECK_GE(demux_state_, WEBP_DEMUX_PARSED_HEADER)

so that demux_state_ is compared with WEBP_DEMUX_PARSED_HEADER

consistently.

entry.title: IndexedDB: reroute quota checks through IndexedDBBucketContext
entry.content:
Rerouting these checks through IndexedDBBucketContext removes one more

dependency from the bucket sequence to the main sequence and allows

coalescing of quota checks.



* Coalescing checks (creating a queue that is drained with just one

trip to the quota manager thread) has the potential to reduce thread

hopping. This will also eliminate an existing race between quota

checks and transaction commits when multiple transactions

coexist. [1]



* We can take the opportunity to fudge the checks a little in order

to reduce the overhead required to write to the database. This will

improve performance for the use case of many small transactions at

the cost of potentially overstepping quota by at most

kAcceptableQuotaErrorMargin. See investigation in crbug.com/1436031

The algorithm being used here is to "remember" any excess quota for

a while, i.e. 30 seconds. The amount that the bucket context has

the authority to approve decays linearly over those 30 seconds.



* Pre-warm the bucket space cache, i.e. check the bucket space in the

quota manager when a transaction first puts a value, in addition

to when it commits (the commit check will have been cached most

likely)



[1] Because both transactions' quota checks may be processed before

the first transaction commits, the latter quota check would not

take into account the earlier transaction's disk usage.



Bug: 1474996,1436031
